contentrichtext.text: This page lists the status of provincial articles to be formatted as part of the [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Philippine LGUs|WikiProject Philippine LGUs]]. ==Almost OK== *[[Biliran]]: Needs more People and Culture info, and climate. ==Started== *[[Albay]]: No climate. Needs more people and culture. History section needs to be rewritten to be chronological. *[[Antique, Philippines|Antique]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography, and most History. *[[Apayao]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography *[[Batangas]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography, History, Links. *[[Benguet]]: No Physical Geography *[[Bohol]]: No Culture and Economy. *[[Bulacan]]: No History. *[[Camarines Sur]]: No Culture, Economy, History. *[[Cavite]]: No People and Culture, Economy, History. *[[Cebu]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography. *[[Davao province|Davao]]: No People and Culture, Physical Geography. Needs more history and tourist attractions. *[[Laguna province|Laguna]]: No People and Culture, Economy; little History and Links. *[[Marinduque]]: No People and Culture, Economy, History and Links. *[[Palawan]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography, History. *[[Pangasinan]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography, some History *[[Quezon]]: No People and Culture, Links. *[[Rizal]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography. *[[Romblon]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography. *[[Siquijor]]: No Culture, and Economy. *[[Southern Leyte]]: No People and Culture, Economy, Physical Geography, History, Links. ==No seal== *[[Sarangani]]
